  "summary": "Typosquat with install-time host reconnaissance and exfiltration",
  "details": "The package name impersonates the legitimate Solana Labs scope and ethers.js library. On install, package.json runs `node install.js` as a postinstall hook. install.js collects host identity information (hostname references at lines 10, 35, 37) and transmits it to an external endpoint via POST/curl (lines 56, 116). This is the canonical install-time exfiltration shape for a name-confusion package — the package has no plausible legitimate purpose under the @solana-labs scope and uses the postinstall hook to fingerprint and report installer machines.",
